f the metal-rich\nand metal-poor peaks depends exclusively on the galaxy assembly and star\nformation history: galaxies in denser environments and/or early types galaxies\nshow a larger fraction of metal-poor GCs, while galaxies with a sparse merger\nhistory and/or late type galaxies are dominated by metal-rich GCs. 4) The GC\nmetallicity bimodality disappears for galaxy masses below M(star)~1e9, and for\nz>2.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 7 Nov 2012 00:58:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-12"}
